il-docs/examples/jubilee</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/jubilee/">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/email-docs/assets/images/examples/jubilee.png&quot; alt=&quot;Jubilee&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Michael Foley</name><email>mifoley@fordham.edu</email></author><category term="examples" /></entry><entry><title type="html">GSE Newsletter</title><link href="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/gse-newsletter/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="GSE Newsletter" /><published>2017-02-14T00:00:00-05:00</published><updated>2017-02-14T00:00:00-05:00</updated><id>http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/gse-newsletter</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/gse-newsletter/">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/email-docs/assets/images/examples/gse-newsletter.png&quot; alt=&quot;Graduate School of Education Newsletter&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Michael Foley</name><email>mifoley@fordham.edu</email></author><category term="examples" /></entry><entry><title type="html">UGE Dean Solicitation</title><link href="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/deans-letter/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="UGE Dean Solicitation" /><published>2017-02-14T00:00:00-05:00</published><updated>2017-02-14T00:00:00-05:00</updated><id>http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/deans-letter</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/deans-letter/">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/email-docs/assets/images/examples/deansletter.png&quot; alt=&quot;UGE Dean Solicitation&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Michael Foley</name><email>mifoley@fordham.edu</email></author><category term="examples" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Athletics initiatives announcement letter</title><link href="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/athletics-letter/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Athletics initiatives announcement letter" /><published>2017-02-14T00:00:00-05:00</published><updated>2017-02-14T00:00:00-05:00</updated><id>http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/athletics-letter</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/examples/athletics-letter/">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/email-docs/assets/images/examples/athletics-initiatives.png&quot; alt=&quot;Athletics initiatives&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Michael Foley</name><email>mifoley@fordham.edu</email></author><category term="examples" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Schedule an email</title><link href="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/checklist/schedule/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Schedule an email" /><published>2017-02-13T00:00:00-05:00</published><updated>2017-02-13T00:00:00-05:00</updated><id>http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/checklist/schedule</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/checklist/schedule/">&lt;p&gt;This is the minimum content needed to put an email on the calendar and should be done as early as possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0;&quot;&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job number and name&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proposed send date&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Measurable goals&lt;/strong&gt; for the email&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target audience&lt;/strong&gt;, which should include the criteria for the list. Amanda will let you know if you will need to have a list pulled or if we can pull the list directly in Mailchimp.&lt;/p&gt;

    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example target audiences:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;All Gabelli undergrads who live in NYC plus 50 miles.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;All young alumni who have made a gift in the past but have not given this year.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;All former basketball players and athletics donors.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</content><author><name>Michael Foley</name><email>mifoley@fordham.edu</email></author><category term="checklist" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Other things to consider</title><link href="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/checklist/other/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Other things to consider" /><published>2017-02-13T00:00:00-05:00</published><updated>2017-02-13T00:00:00-05:00</updated><id>http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/checklist/other</id><content type="html" xml:base="http://fordhamumc.github.io/emaildocs/email-docs/checklist/other/">&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event website&lt;/strong&gt;: Make sure the event website is up-to-date before the send date.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reminder emails&lt;/strong&gt;: Does the client want to send a reminder email?
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Audience: Who should receive the reminder? Everyone (not recommended for lists larger than 10,000), people who opened, or some other segment&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Content: Do they want to change email body?&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Attendees/donors: We will need a list of people who have signed up/donated/etc so we can exclude them from the reminder.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Subject: The subject must be different from the original, even if slightly, to avoid being combined with the original message.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Social media links&lt;/strong&gt;: The social media links in the footer of each email are set to the alumni or University accounts by default. These can be changed or removed if requested.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purchased lists&lt;/strong&gt;: We cannot send to purchased lists. These have a notoriously high abuse rate and can affect our sender rating.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outside lists&lt;/strong&gt;: If a client or guest speaker maintains their own list of mostly non-Fordham constituents we discourage mailing to their list. Sending Fordham-branded emails to these lists tend to have low open rates and create confusion among the recipients. We find it is more effective for the client to message their own list and we can provide any images or copy they may need.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</content><author><name>Michael Foley</name><email>mifoley@fordham.edu</email></author><category term="checklist" /></entry></feed>
